      "text": "Which of the following statements is true regarding the differences between a light and an electron microscope?",
      "options": [
        {
          "label": "A",
          "text": "Light microscope has a magnification of 10,000x, while that of an electron microscope is 1,00,000x.",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "B",
          "text": "The resolution of a light microscope is 0.2 \u03bcm and that of a transmission electron microscope is 0.2 nm.",
          "correct": true
        },
        {
          "label": "C",
          "text": "Light microscope uses a single lens while an electron microscope uses an electromagnet.",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "D",
          "text": "Both operate in a vacuum medium.",
          "correct": false
        }
      ],
      "correct_answer": "B. The resolution of a light microscope is 0.2 \u03bcm and that of a transmission electron microscope is 0.2 nm.",
      "question_images": [],
      "explanation_images": [
        "https://image.prepladder.com/notes/96B7sZdgYfYrgzptbYLF1744405366.png",
        "https://image.prepladder.com/notes/NQGqoMVqsYvArdkugsVh1747211676.png",
        "https://image.prepladder.com/notes/MLwbxjjADI5U3jxBZTWp1744402180.png",
        "https://image.prepladder.com/notes/G4dte5EzS3lZ4Rm5X7Kq1744403845.png"
      ],
      "explanation": "<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:626px\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Light Microscope:</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Electron Microscope:</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\u00a0</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Light from the sources passes through the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"c02ad9ae0f1692777198d76afc93c4\">specimen</span> after being focused by the condenser, and the lenses collect it.</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Electron microscopes use electrons to visualise the specimens.</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\u00a0</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>It is set up in an air medium.</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>It is set up in a vacuum medium.</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>(Option D ruled out)</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Types: bright-field, phase-contrast, <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"6bd54dfc48169277718674cd08e586\">differential</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"f087a3103216927771903f59008962\">interference</span> contrast, dark-field, and fluorescence.</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Types- TEM- Transmission <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d416281a201692777187899c00aed8\">Electron</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"195d6a11ca16927771927a92617498\">Microscope</span> and SEM- Transmission <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d416281a201692777187899c00aed8\">Electron</span> Microscopy</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\u00a0</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>A compound <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"441ff5375b169277719127eec94584\">light microscope</span> contains two types of lenses- objective and ocular- that combine to <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"079e4e7d2b1692777191aef396bfd3\">magnify</span> the image.</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Electromagnets function as lenses.</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>(Option C ruled out)</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Magnification</strong>: <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"7b1f175723169277719459db16938e\">Ocular</span> lenses- 10 to 30x; Objective lenses- 10 to 100x. The product of the two gives the total <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"279228dffd1692777191c834a27177\">magnification</span> (1000x.)</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Magnification:</strong> 15x, up to about 1,00,000x with an SEM and up to 50 million times with a TEM.</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>(Option A ruled out)</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Resolution: </strong>0.2 \u03bcm.</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Resolution: </strong>The <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"91277e8b181692777197dca5dca9cc\">resolving power</span> of TEM is 0.2 nm and SEM ranges between 0.5 and 4 nm.</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>(Option B)</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Structures are visualised using contrast.</li>\n<li>Staining, phase contrast, <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"6bd54dfc48169277718674cd08e586\">differential</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"f087a3103216927771903f59008962\">interference</span> contrast, dark field, and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"da0e2a00fa1692777202d6e2054b26\">fluorescence</span> improve contrast.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>TEM- <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d69fe0ec841692777194ae6ac401a2\">osmic</span> acid, permanganate, uranium, lanthanum, or lead salts are used for staining.</li>\n<li>SEM- the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"c02ad9ae0f1692777198d76afc93c4\">specimen</span> is coated with a thin film of a <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"6e8ada09fa1692777189bfbace851a\">heavy metal</span> like gold.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\u00a0</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n\n\n<p style='font-size: 10px; color: #808080; font-style: italic;'></p>",
