      "correct_answer": "C. The whole system of an electron microscope functions in a vacuum.",
      "question_images": [],
      "explanation_images": [],
      "explanation": "<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:NaN\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Transmission <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d416281a201692777187899c00aed8\">Electron</span> Microscopy</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Scanning <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d416281a201692777187899c00aed8\">Electron</span> Microscopy</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Cells and cell structures are visualised at very high <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"279228dffd1692777191c834a27177\">magnification</span> and resolution</li>\n<li>The <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"91277e8b181692777197dca5dca9cc\">resolving power</span> of a <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5fb42dc4111692777200bd7d0f6f93\">TEM</span> is much greater than that of a light microscope. Therefore, one can view structures at the molecular level.</li>\n<li>Uses a <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"ef914bdb201692777202c455236ca8\">wavelength</span> much shorter than visible light</li>\n<li>The <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"91277e8b181692777197dca5dca9cc\">resolving power</span> is 0.2 nm (light <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"195d6a11ca16927771927a92617498\">microscope</span> = 0.2 \u00b5m.) <strong>(Option D ruled out)</strong></li>\n<li>As the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"55b31d659b16927771958a15837b10\">penetrating</span> power of an <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d416281a201692777187899c00aed8\">electron</span> is very low, thin sections are needed, unless only external structures of an organism are to be studied. <strong>(Option A ruled out)</strong></li>\n<li>Sections should be stabilised and stained to be examined</li>\n<li>Stains used - <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d69fe0ec841692777194ae6ac401a2\">osmic</span> acid, permanganate, uranium, lanthanum, or lead salts</li>\n<li>Intact cells or cell components can be observed directly in the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5fb42dc4111692777200bd7d0f6f93\">TEM</span> by a technique called negative staining</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Used for <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"208cf74d74169277719486afd05eb3\">optimal</span> three-dimensional examination of cells</li>\n<li>Magnification ranges from as low as 15x, up to about 1,00,000x, but only the object\u2019s surface can be visualized <strong>(Option B ruled out)</strong></li>\n<li>The <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"c02ad9ae0f1692777198d76afc93c4\">specimen</span> is coated with a thin film of a <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"6e8ada09fa1692777189bfbace851a\">heavy metal</span> like gold</li>\n<li>Electrons are scattered from the metal coating. They are collected and projected on a monitor, producing an image</li>\n<li>Large specimens can be studied with an excellent focus</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n\n\n<p style='font-size: 10px; color: #808080; font-style: italic;'></p>",
